    <item>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1424</guid>
      <link>https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1424</link>
      <title>PR: Move stuff about - @KevinRansom</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Because I am a frivolous and somwewhat foolish young man (ahem ... I am I tell ya).  When doing the netstandard20 stuff I put two projects in the same directory.  When DisableArcade=1 is set then this causes the tooling to overwrite the project.assets.json file created by the nuget build tasks, when both files are created.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want my opinion this is an sdk build bug ... but I suppose only one project per directory is fairly strong convention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This fix just moves Netstandard20 into it's own top level project directory, thus eliminating the overwrite.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Jun 2021 23:22:22 Z</pubDate>
    </item>
