    <item>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1397</guid>
      <link>https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1397</link>
      <title>PR: Use NameInCode to backtick-escape necessary F# completions when inserting - @cartermp</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Before this change, some F# completions that require backticks would show up correctly in the completion list, but would insert as the display name rather than the &amp;quot;name in code&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After this change, the display remains the same, but when inserting the completion, the &lt;code&gt;NameInCode&lt;/code&gt; value is used, which has backticks. This is what we do in the VS tools for F# as well (although it is a much more complex process... )&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 08 Jun 2021 17:23:52 Z</pubDate>
    </item>
