    <item>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1393</guid>
      <link>https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/pull/1393</link>
      <title>PR: load script extensions from NuGet packages - @brettfo</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a purely source-based version of loading interactive extensions.  The existing binary-based one loads all assemblies from &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;NUGET_PACKAGE_PATH&amp;gt;/interactive-extensions/dotnet/*.dll&lt;/code&gt; so this one plays off of that scenario by simply loading and executing the file &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;NUGET_PACKAGE_PATH&amp;gt;/interactive-extensions/dotnet/extension.dib&lt;/code&gt; if it was found.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This takes advantage of the fact that a multi-cell &lt;code&gt;.dib&lt;/code&gt; file can be executed with a single call to &lt;code&gt;SubmitCode&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Jun 2021 21:42:03 Z</pubDate>
    </item>
